tafsir[19]{c,v,t}:
  80,1,"And from his narration on the authority of Ibn 'Abbas that he said regarding the interpretation of Allah's saying (He frowned): '(He frowned) He says: Muhammad (pbuh) showed a stern face (and turned away) his face"
  80,3,"(What could inform thee) O Muhammad (but that he might) i.e. the blind man (grow (in grace)) became righteous through the admonitions of the Qur'an"
  80,6,"(Unto him thou payest regard) you turn your face to them."
  80,7,"(Yet it is not thy concern if he grow not (in grace)) it is not your concern if these three men do not believe in Allah's divine Oneness."
  80,8,"(But as for him who cometh unto thee with earnest purpose) hastening for goodness"
  80,10,"(From him thou) O Muhammad (art distracted) being busy with those three men."
  80,13,"(On honoured leaves) He says: the Qur'an is written on scrolls made of skin which are honoured in the sight of Allah"
  80,15,"((Set down) by scribes) written by scribes"
  80,16,"(Noble) in the sight of Allah and surrendered to Him (and righteous) truthful; these are the keepers of the nether heaven."
  80,18,"(From what thing doth He create him?) He says: let him think about his own person: from what did He create him as a living being?"
  80,26,"(Then split the earth in clefts) through plants"
  80,27,"(And cause the grain) all kinds of grain (to grow therein) in the earth"
  80,28,"(And grapes and green fodder"
  80,29,"And olive trees and palm-trees"
  80,30,"And garden closes of thick foliage"
  80,31,"And fruits) different kinds of fruit (and grasses) and fodder; and it also said this means: straw:"
  80,32,"(Provision for you) the grains are of benefit to you (and your cattle) and fodder is of benefit to your cattle."
  80,35,"(And his mother) and will also flee from his mother (and his father"
  80,37,"(Every man that day) on the Day of Judgement (will have concern enough to make him heedless (of others)) to keep him preoccupied from others."